benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts - Retrieve an account by external key

covered: Valid Request: Multiple scenarios verify successful GET by externalKey with varying query parameters (balance, CBA, audit) and default behavior.
Not Found / Empty Data Handling: Tests for account-not-found (TC06) and empty-database (TC17) ensuring 404 behavior.

Query Parameters: Broad coverage for valid/invalid combinations of query parameters (accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, audit) plus extra parameter handling (TC16) and boundary cases (TC18/TC19).
Authorization: Tests for missing and invalid authentication tokens (TC11, TC12) covering authentication failures.
Security & Input Validation: Tests for SQL injection (TC14), XSS (TC15), and invalid formats/values (TC08, TC09, TC10).
Resilience & Error Handling: Tests for service unavailability (TC13), data inconsistency (TC24 giving 502), and timeout (TC25 giving 504).
Performance/Load: Tests for response time under normal load (TC20) and under peak load/concurrency (TC21).
Boundary/Compatibility: Boundary length tests (TC18, TC19) and backward compatibility/regression (TC22, TC23).
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination behavior, which may be relevant if multiple accounts or paginated results were possible in other endpoints or future changes.
Caching Behavior: No tests validate caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or related caching behavior for this GET endpoint.
Rate Limiting: No explicit tests for rate limiting/throttling when bursts of requests occur.
Authorization (403): No test specifically asserting 403 Forbidden due to insufficient permissions (only 401 Unauthorized is covered).
Internal Server Error coverage: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario beyond 503/502/504 (may be useful to cover unexpected server errors).
recommendations: Add a test for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient permissions scenarios beyond missing/invalid tokens.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate behavior under burst traffic.
Add caching-related tests to verify presence and correctness of caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) if applicable.
Add a 500 Internal Server Error test case to ensure graceful handling of generic server failures.
If pagination could become relevant in future (e.g., listing multiple accounts or related endpoints), add a dedicated pagination test to verify proper behavior with large datasets.
Consider consolidating and documenting expected error response bodies for common error codes to ensure consistency across failures.
